The paper deals with a communication channel model corrupted by Wiener phase noise and additive white Gaussian noise, which is a common problem in wireless communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also introduces a discrete-time channel model and discusses the performance of a multi-sample receiver, which falls under the category of cs.COMM (Communications and Networking). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of oversampling on the performance of the receiver, which is related to signal processing and could be categorized under cs.SI (Signal Processing) or cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper also discusses the potential application of the results in control systems, which could be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
